description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The BANES Intensive Service are looking for a fulltime Recovery Coordinator to join the team on a substantive basis. The post holder will be based at Hillview Lodge at the Royal United Hospital in Bath. If you are looking for an opportunity to develop your clinical skills and are passionate about improving people&#39;s experience of mental health, then this is a fantastic opportunity to work in a challenging and diverse role. You will be joining an experienced and friendly multi-disciplinary team in a supportive working environment, with a visible and accessible management team who prioritises supportive supervision and a commitment to staff training and development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The BANES Intensive Service is responsible for providing assessments, home treatment and support to individuals with intensive mental health care needs. The team work with GPs, PCLS, Recovery, EI, AMHPS, IAPT, inpatient services and general wards improving mental health recognition and treatment and avoiding hospital admission when possible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working within multidisciplinary mental health teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with people with mental health issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Passion and commitment to high standards of  care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication and organisational skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:   &lt;span&gt;Jo Mahoney, Team Manager or Phil Rhodes, Access Services Manager on 01225 362700.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
